The paper focuses on mobile edge caching, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication systems. Therefore, cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a linear model and uses regression algorithms to predict content popularity, which falls under the scope of machine learning and data science. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of $H_{\infty}$ filter, which is a control theory concept, indicating that cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible sub-categories.
